cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a new matrix approximation method for efficient second order optimization, specifically in the context of training deep neural networks using AdaGrad. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper deals with optimization algorithms and matrix computations. Additionally, since the proposed method is applied to image classification tasks, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely category. Finally, since the paper deals with optimization algorithms and deep learning, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category.
